Class AbstractSubscriber

  • java.lang.Object
    • baseEntities.AbstractEntity<java.lang.Integer>
      • subscribers.AbstractSubscriber
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IEntity<java.lang.Integer>, java.lang.Comparable<AbstractSubscriber>, ISubscriber
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AlphaSubscriber, BetaSubscriber, DefaultSubscriber, GammaSubscriber

    public abstract class AbstractSubscriber
extends AbstractEntity<java.lang.Integer>
implements java.lang.Comparable<AbstractSubscriber>, ISubscriber
    Package-Protected class that implements the "State Design Pattern". It forces all implementing classes to define an interchangeable state that is encapsulated in the concrete classes. This allows for easy incorporation of various states that can define unique logic. These classes should not be used outside of this package.
    Author:
    qjames2, tzhu63, zzhan746, mgianco2, rblack43
